					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment. </support>
								<extent>349 folios<dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>337</height>
										<width>258</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<width>172</width>
										<height>220</height>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>349 folios (+ 2 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and 3 at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>35 quires of mostly 10 leaves each, apart from: i8, xv8, viii12, x-xii12, xxvi12, xvi6, xxxv7.  </p>
									<p>The quires are signed with Hebrew letters on the first and last pages.  </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Folio 1r-1v and last few leaves, 346r-349v are not fully preserved. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="2" ruledLines="22" writtenLines="22">
									<p>Samuel, Kings, Ezekiel, Joel, Micah and Haggai begin a new column, and Isaiah commences a new leaf. </p>
									<p>The margin of the manuscript contains the ḳeri and the beginning of the Hafṭarot. </p>
									<p>The titles of the books are written at the top of every recto and the leaves are numbered with Hebrew letters.</p>
									<p>Pricking and ruling (of bifolios, with hard-point on the hair-side) visible. </p>
									<p>Visible difference between flesh and hair side. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Sefardi square script, punctuated. <name type="person" role="scribe">Ben Mosheh ha-Leṿi</name>: inscribed with his name in partailly preserved colophon on folio 349v : ב"ר מ[שה?] הלוי זצ"ל (for manuscripts of the same scribe see e.g. <ref target="Allony_1957" type="number">23, 654</ref>). </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<decoDesc>
							<summary>Ornamental pen and ink designs of the chain pattern at the end of some of the books.</summary>
							<decoNote type="other">
								<locus n="160v, 205r"/>Ornamental pen and ink designs of the chain pattern at the end of some of the books.</decoNote>
						</decoDesc>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p> 	Post-1600; black leather Harleian binding; the Harley coat of arms in the centre.</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
